   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">The procedure for removing the bottom mounted IP kit is
the same for all types of IP ratings.</p>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Unscrew the screws <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(A)</b> from the clips <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(C)</b>. Remove the screws <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(A)</b>, the washers <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(B)</b>, the clips <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(C)</b> and the front grid <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(D)</b> from the transport units.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../../Images/Bottom_IP_Kit_Remove-front_0000392126.svg"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Remove the back grid <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(E)</b> in the same way as the
front grid <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(D)</b>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../../Images/Bottom_IP_Kit_Remove-back_0000392125.svg"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for gland plates (Not used):</b> Remove the screws
attaching the gland plates <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(F)</b> to the sockets at the locations <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(G)</b>.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Slide out and remove any bottom grids, filter mats and/or
gland plates <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(F)</b> from under the transport unit.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <note class="- topic/note ">Depends on the system configuration, the selected IP rating
and terminal/cable inlet placement. See the general arrangement drawing
for more information.</note>
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../../Images/Bottom_IP_Kit_Remove-plates_0000392124.svg"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </info>
         </step>
      </steps>
